tionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2533584\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Dez 05, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104wyk1665702998988.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/wyk1665702998988.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/wyk1665702998988.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"wyk1665702998988\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n               \n Compile and Test the Migrated Application \n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Compile and test the migrated application to identify and correct possible changes in the way the application functions.\n </p>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"wyk1665702998988__li_d31163e1_d31164e1_d31165e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"wyk1665702998988__p_d68417e1_d68418e1_d68419e1\">Compile the application in Uniface <span class=\"ph\">10.4</span>.  </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">Use the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/all /war</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">/cmi=1</code> command line switch to compile all objects, generate CMI\n                  files, and generate warnings. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"sww1665702625667.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/sww1665702625667.html\" title=\"Compile all types of compilable main development objects, including components, modeled entities, and global objects.\">/all</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dkq1665702626173.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dkq1665702626173.html\" title=\"Specifies whether compiled module information is generated when compiling objects with a command line switch.\">/cmi</a>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wyk1665702998988__p_d68420e1_d68421e1_d68422e1\">For example, for Uniface 9 imports you may see\n                  extra compilation warnings because ProcScript entries are compiled\n                  differently.</p>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"wyk1665702998988__li_d31166e1_d31167e1_d31168e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"wyk1665702998988__p_d68423e1_d68424e1_d68425e1\">Check the compilation logs. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">Pay special attention to warnings or errors that you did not get when compiling in\n                  earlier Uniface versions. Fix problems when needed.</p>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"wyk1665702998988__li_d31169e1_d31170e1_d31171e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Run the application and test it. Fix any functional issues that you discover in either Uniface <span class=\"ph\">10.4</span> or in the version you are migrating from. \n \n </span>\n</li></ol></section>\n<section class=\"section result body required-cleanup-multiple-ol-elements-in-topic-body\" id=\"wyk1665702998988__result_w3044ab1b5b3_w3045ab1b5_w3046ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"wyk1665702998988__p_d68426e1_d68427e1_d68428e1\">Next steps:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wyk1665702998988__li_d31172e1_d31173e1_d31174e1\">If you fix issues in your earlier version of Uniface, repeat the previous task: <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"spp1665702999061.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/spp1665702999061.html\" title=\"When your Uniface 9 application is ready to migrate, export the repository objects, then import into Uniface 10. Whenever Uniface detects that there are records that need to be migrated, it automatically starts the migration process. This may also occur if a previous migration process was interrupted.\">Migrate Repository Objects from Uniface 9</a>.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"wyk1665702998988__li_d31175e1_d31176e1_d31177e1\">If you fix issues in Uniface <span class=\"ph\">10.4</span>, compile and test again.\n </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533584\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533584\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Compile and Test the Migrated Application Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Dez 05, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Compile and Test the Migrated Application Compile and test the migrated application to identify and correct possible changes in the way the application functions. Compile the application in Uniface 10.4 . Use the /all /war /cmi=1 command line switch to compile all objects, generate CMI files, and generate warnings. For more information, see /all and /cmi . For example, for Uniface 9 imports you may see extra compilation warnings because ProcScript entries are compiled differently. Check the compilation logs. Pay special attention to warnings or errors that you did not get when compiling in earlier Uniface versions. Fix problems when needed. Run the application and test it. Fix any functional issues that you discover in either Uniface 10.4 or in the version you are migrating from. Next steps: If you fix issues in your earlier version of Uniface, repeat the previous task: Migrate Repository Objects from Uniface 9 . If you fix issues in Uniface 10.4 , compile and test again. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}